# Analysis of the Main Target Image

## Count & Layers
The structure consists of approximately 14 blocks arranged in multiple layers:
- Base layer: Red arch blocks and green rectangular blocks
- Middle layer: Blue cube, yellow cylinders, orange/red cubes
- Top layer: Yellow tall blocks, triangular roof pieces

## Spatial Relationships
The structure appears to be a small building complex with:
1. A main section consisting of red arch blocks as the base
2. Blue and orange/red cube blocks forming small house-like structures with triangular roofs
3. Yellow cylinders and yellow rectangular blocks in the middle
4. Green vertical blocks supporting the structure
5. A separate small red arch block with triangular roof to the right of the main structure

# Blocks Needed from Dictionary

Based on the target image, I need the following blocks:

1. Red arch blocks (indices 1 and 2) - for the base of the structures
2. Blue cube (index 4) - for the left "house" body
3. Orange cube (index 5) - for the right "house" body
4. Red cube (index 6) - for one of the structures
5. Green vertical blocks (index 7) - for support pillars
6. Yellow horizontal blocks (index 8 and 10) - for horizontal elements
7. Yellow vertical blocks (index 9) - for the tall yellow elements
8. Yellow half-cylinder blocks (index 11) - for the curved elements
9. Orange triangular roof pieces (indices 14, 15, 16) - for the roof elements

# Assembly Order

```
{
    Step1: Move block with index 1
    Step2: Move block with index 2
    Step3: Move block with index 2
    Step4: Move block with index 11
    Step5: Move block with index 11
    Step6: Move block with index 4
    Step7: Move block with index 6
    Step8: Move block with index 5
    Step9: Move block with index 14
    Step10: Move block with index 15
    Step11: Move block with index 7
    Step12: Move block with index 7
    Step13: Move block with index 9
    Step14: Move block with index 9
    Step15: Move block with index 1
    Step16: Move block with index 16
}
```

This assembly order starts with the base structures, adds the middle elements, then builds upward to complete the structure, finishing with the separate small house structure on the right.
